* Get workspace sectors * arg1: WorkspaceStruct (optional, if omitted then uses this ship's workspace) * gResult: array of sectors f001: if notis datatype[ $arg1 ] == DATATYPE_ARRAY $tShipStruct=[THIS] -> get local variable: name='wwsl.T2.config' $arg1=$tShipStruct[5] end $tSector=$arg1[1] $tJumps=$arg1[2] $tInclude=$arg1[4] $tExclude=$arg1[5] $tRace=[THIS] -> get owner race $tFlags=[TRUE] skip if$tRace == Player $tFlags=[FALSE] $gResult=$tSector -> find all sectors within $tJumps jumps: Only known sectors=$tFlags $tIndex=size of array $tInclude while$tIndex > 0 dec $tIndex= $tSector=$tInclude[$tIndex] skip iffind $tSector in array: $gResult append $tSector to array $gResult end $tIndex=size of array $tExclude while$tIndex > 0 dec $tIndex= $tSector=$tExclude[$tIndex] $tEntry=get index of $tSector in array $gResult offset=-1 + 1 do if $tEntry >= 0 remove element from array $gResult at index $tEntry end endsub
* Get logistical range of target object * In: $f002.GetRange.InArgs ARRAY(station, ware, B|S, token) * Out: $f002.GetRange.Out f002.GetRange: $f002.GetRange.Out=null resize array $f002.GetRange.InArgs to 4 $f002.GetRange.Station=$f002.GetRange.InArgs[0] $f002.GetRange.Ware=$f002.GetRange.InArgs[1] $f002.GetRange.Op=$f002.GetRange.InArgs[2] $f002.GetRange.Token=$f002.GetRange.InArgs[3] $tStation.Amount=$f002.GetRange.Station -> get ware storage percentage: ware=$f002.GetRange.Ware skip if$f002.GetRange.Op == 'B' $tStation.Amount=100 - $tStation.Amount @ $tAgo=[THIS] -> call script wwsl.T2.function : #Fn=503 arg1=$f002.GetRange.Station arg2=$f002.GetRange.Ware arg3=$f002.GetRange.Op arg4=$f002.GetRange.Token arg5=null skip if$tAgo AND $tAgo >= 0 AND $tAgo <= 3600 $tAgo=3600 $f002.GetRange.Out=$tStation.Amount * $tAgo / 3600 + $tStation.Amount @ $f002.GetRange.Out=[THIS] -> call script wwsl.T2.util.formatNumber : Number=$f002.GetRange.Out Decimals=10 $tmp=random value from 10 to 100 - 1 * Just for debug reason $f002.GetRange.Out=sprintf: fmt='%s.%s amnt=%s ago=%s', $f002.GetRange.Out, $tmp, $tStation.Amount, $tAgo, null endsub

* Combine arrays into the table * All arrays must be of same size * In: arg1 - array #1 will has [X][0] coord * In: arg2 - array #2 will has [X][1] coord * In: arg3 - array #3 (optional) will has [X][2] coord * In: arg4 - array #4 (optional) will has [X][3] coord * In: arg5 - array #5 (optional) will has [X][4] coord * Out: $gResult - table-array or null if arguments are not correct f054: skip ifis datatype[ $arg1 ] == DATATYPE_ARRAY endsub skip ifis datatype[ $arg2 ] == DATATYPE_ARRAY endsub $tSrc.ArrayList=create new array, arguments=$arg1, $arg2, null, null, null ifis datatype[ $arg3 ] == DATATYPE_ARRAY append $arg3 to array $tSrc.ArrayList ifis datatype[ $arg4 ] == DATATYPE_ARRAY append $arg4 to array $tSrc.ArrayList ifis datatype[ $arg5 ] == DATATYPE_ARRAY append $arg5 to array $tSrc.ArrayList end end end * Test all arrays have same size * If at least one source array has different size then exit with no result $tCount.Rows=size of array $arg1 $tCount.Cols=size of array $tSrc.ArrayList $tIndex.Col=0 while$tIndex.Col < $tCount.Cols $Dummy.Array=$tSrc.ArrayList[$tIndex.Col] $Dummy.Count=size of array $Dummy.Array skip if$Dummy.Count == $tCount.Rows endsub inc $tIndex.Col= end @ =wait 1 ms * Build combined 2D array $gResult=array alloc: size=$tCount.Rows $tIndex.Row=0 while$tIndex.Row < $tCount.Rows $tRow=array alloc: size=$tCount.Cols $gResult[$tIndex.Row] = $tRow $tIndex.Col=0 while$tIndex.Col < $tCount.Cols $Dummy=$tSrc.ArrayList[$tIndex.Col][$tIndex.Row] $tRow[$tIndex.Col] = $Dummy inc $tIndex.Col= end inc $tIndex.Row= skip if$tIndex.Row mod 10 @ =wait 1 ms end endsub * End of f054
* Get table column values as array * In: arg1 - table-array * In: arg2 - index of column to extract * gResult: column values as array or null if arguments aren't correct f055: skip ifis datatype[ $arg1 ] == DATATYPE_ARRAY endsub skip ifis datatype[ $arg2 ] == DATATYPE_INT endsub skip if$arg2 >= 0 endsub $tCount.Rows=size of array $arg1 $Dummy.Array=array alloc: size=$tCount.Rows $tIndex.Row=0 while$tIndex.Row < $tCount.Rows $tRow=$arg1[$tIndex.Row] skip ifis datatype[ $tRow ] == DATATYPE_ARRAY endsub $tCount.Cols=size of array $tRow skip if$arg2 < $tCount.Cols endsub $Dummy.Array[$tIndex.Row] = $tRow[$arg2] inc $tIndex.Row= skip if$tIndex.Row mod 10 @ =wait 1 ms end $gResult=$Dummy.Array endsub * End of f055
* Combine two arrays into new one * In: arg1 - array #1 will be at start of a new array * In: arg2 - array #2 will be at end of the new array * gResult: new array or null if arguments aren't arrays f056: skip ifis datatype[ $arg1 ] == DATATYPE_ARRAY endsub skip ifis datatype[ $arg2 ] == DATATYPE_ARRAY endsub $Dummy.Count=size of array $arg1 $Dummy2.Count=size of array $arg2 $tCount=$Dummy.Count + $Dummy2.Count $gResult=array alloc: size=$tCount $Dummy.Index=$Dummy.Count - 1 copy array $arg1 index 0 ... $Dummy.Index into array $gResult at index 0 $Dummy2.Index=$Dummy2.Count - 1 copy array $arg2 index 0 ... $Dummy2.Index into array $gResult at index $Dummy.Count endsub * End of f056

* Get point at desired distance of P1 lied on vector between P1 and P2 * Note: This works with 100m precision! * In: arg1 - array x,y,z of P1 * In: arg2 - Not implemented! array x,y,z of P2 (optional) * If omitted then P2 is 0,0,0 * In: arg3 - desired distance * gResult: array x,y,z of result point f058: skip ifis datatype[ $arg1 ] == DATATYPE_ARRAY endsub *skip ifis datatype[ $arg2 ] == DATATYPE_ARRAY $arg2=create new array, arguments=0, 0, 0, null, null skip ifis datatype[ $arg3 ] == DATATYPE_INT endsub $tP1.X=$arg1[0] $tP1.Y=$arg1[1] $tP1.Z=$arg1[2] *$tP2.X=$arg2[0] *$tP2.Y=$arg2[1] *$tP2.Z=$arg2[2] $gResult=create new array, arguments=0, 0, 0, null, null $tP.H=get distance: position array1=$arg1 array2=$arg2 $tP.H=$tP.H / 100 $tR.H=$tP.H + $arg3 / 100 if$tP.H != 0 $Dummy2=$tR.H * $tP1.X / $tP.H $gResult[0] = $Dummy2 $Dummy2=$tR.H * $tP1.Y / $tP.H $gResult[1] = $Dummy2 $Dummy2=$tR.H * $tP1.Z / $tP.H $gResult[2] = $Dummy2 end endsub * End of f058
* Create & init new data structure * arg1: struct ID (WareStruct, WorkspaceStruct, StatStruct, ShipStruct, etc... * gResult: data struct f506: skip ifis datatype[ $arg1 ] == DATATYPE_STRING endsub if$arg1 == 'WareStruct' $gResult=array alloc: size=8 $gResult[0] = 'WareStruct-3.01'

* Switch ship to specified program. * arg1: target program number * gResut: TRUE - ok, FALSE - couldn't switch to specified program f510: $gResult=[FALSE] skip ifis datatype[ $arg1 ] == DATATYPE_INT endsub $tShipStruct=[THIS] -> get local variable: name='wwsl.T2.config' if notis datatype[ $tShipStruct ] == DATATYPE_ARRAY @ $tShipStruct=[THIS] -> call script wwsl.T2.function1 : #Fn=506 arg1='ShipStruct' [THIS] ->set local variable: name='wwsl.T2.config' value=$tShipStruct end $tCurrentProgram=$tShipStruct[1] $Program=$tCurrentProgram gosub f510.Program2Ship.Purge $Program=$arg1 gosub f510.Program2Ship.Cache if$tCurrentProgram == 1 @ =[THIS] -> call script wwsl.T2.function0 : #Fn=512 end if$arg1 == 2 gosub GetShipStruct gosub Fix.SwProg.To.2 end $tShipStruct[1] = $arg1 $SIGBUY=SIGNAL_BUYWARE $SIGSELL=SIGNAL_SELWARE if$arg1 < 0 [THIS] ->set ship command/signal SIGNAL_ATTACKED to global default behaviour [THIS] ->set ship command/signal SIGNAL_KILLED to global default behaviour [THIS] ->remove secondary signal: signal=$SIGBUY, name='T2' [THIS] ->remove secondary signal: signal=$SIGSELL, name='T2' else [THIS] ->connect ship command/signal SIGNAL_ATTACKED to script wwsl.T2.signal.attacked with prio 100 [THIS] ->connect ship command/signal SIGNAL_KILLED to script wwsl.T2.signal.killed with prio 10000 [THIS] ->add secondary signal: signal=$SIGBUY, script=wwsl.T2.signal.buyware, prio=200, name='T2' [THIS] ->add secondary signal: signal=$SIGSELL, script=wwsl.T2.signal.sellware, prio=200, name='T2' end $gResult=[TRUE] endsub
